# yapsnap model integrity manifest
# ----------------------------------
# SHA-256 digests of every model file yapsnap may auto-download. Format is the
# standard `sha256sum` layout so this file can be checked directly with:
#
#     sha256sum -c model_checksums.sha256        (run from the cache dir)
#
# yapsnap loads it via load_model_checksums() and verify_checksum() promotes a
# downloaded file into the cache ONLY after its digest matches a line here.
#
# Policy is strict hard-fail, no opt-out:
#   - match            -> file accepted
#   - mismatch         -> hard failure (possible corruption or tampering)
#   - filename absent  -> hard failure (unrecognised auto-download)
#   - manifest missing -> hard failure (nothing can be verified)
#
# This gates AUTO-DOWNLOADS only. A model supplied with --model / KROKO_MODEL
# loads from disk and is never checked here. To auto-download a new model (e.g.
# another Kroko language), add its digest below first; otherwise fetch it
# manually and point --model at its directory.
#
# Verification keys on the BASENAME only, so the path written beside a digest
# is for human reference; `foo.onnx` and `diarization-models/foo.onnx` match
# the same download.
#
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# REGENERATING / ADDING ENTRIES
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# The digests below are real, for the exact released files yapsnap fetches. To
# re-verify them, or to add a new auto-downloadable model, run on a trusted
# machine with network access:
#
#     scripts/gen_hashes.sh --models
#
# It downloads each file from its canonical URL, hashes it, and prints
# manifest-ready lines. Replace a digest only if you have independently
# confirmed the upstream file legitimately changed -- a digest that shifts
# unexpectedly is exactly what this manifest exists to catch.
# ===========================================================================

